org.threadly.concurrent

Interface BlockingQueueConsumer.ConsumerAcceptor<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of item this acceptor will receive
    Enclosing class:
    BlockingQueueConsumer<T>

    public static interface BlockingQueueConsumer.ConsumerAcceptor<T>

    Interface for an implementation which can accept consumed tasks. You must provide an implementation of this interface on construction of the BlockingQueueConsumer.

    Since:
    1.0.0

      void acceptConsumedItem(T item)

    • Method Detail

      • acceptConsumedItem

        void acceptConsumedItem(T item)
                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Called when ever the queue consumer has removed an item from the queue. This call should block until the acceptor is ready for another item.
        Parameters:
        item - Object that was removed from the queue
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - possible exception that could be thrown
